suggestions.tool_tip:
CSS 2              
E[foo]                  
Attribute selector                      
an E element with a "foo" attribute

CSS 2              
E[foo="bar"]          
Attribute selector                      
an E element whose "foo" attribute value is exactly equal to "bar"

CSS 2              
E[foo~="bar"]         
Attribute selector                      
an E element whose "foo" attribute value is a list of space-separated values, one of which is exactly equal to "bar"

CSS 2              
E[hreflang|="en"]     
Attribute selector                      
an E element whose "hreflang" attribute has a hyphen-separated list of values beginning (from the left) with "en"

CSS 3              
E[foo^="bar"]         
Attribute selector                      
an E element whose "foo" attribute value begins exactly with the string "bar"

CSS 3              
E[foo$="bar"]         
Attribute selector                      
an E element whose "foo" attribute value ends exactly with the string "bar"

CSS 3              
E[foo*="bar"]         
Attribute selector                      
an E element whose "foo" attribute value contains the substring "bar"

CSS 2              
E:first-child           
Structural pseudo-class                 
an E element, first child of its parent

CSS 3              
E:root                  
Structural pseudo-class                 
an E element, root of the document

CSS 3              
E:nth-child(n)          
Structural pseudo-class                 
an E element, the n-th child of its parent

CSS 3              
E:nth-last-child(n)     
Structural pseudo-class                 
an E element, the n-th child of its parent, counting from the last one

CSS 3              
E:nth-of-type(n)        
Structural pseudo-class                 
an E element, the n-th sibling of its type

CSS 3              
E:nth-last-of-type(n)   
Structural pseudo-class                 
an E element, the n-th sibling of its type, counting from the last one

CSS 3              
E:last-child            
Structural pseudo-class                 
an E element, last child of its parent

CSS 3              
E:first-of-type         
Structural pseudo-class                 
an E element, first sibling of its type

CSS 3              
E:last-of-type          
Structural pseudo-class                 
an E element, last sibling of its type

CSS 3              
E:only-child            
Structural pseudo-class                 
an E element, only child of its parent

CSS 3              
E:only-of-type          
Structural pseudo-class                 
an E element, only sibling of its type

CSS 3              
E:empty                 
Structural pseudo-class                 
an E element that has no children (including text nodes)

CSS 1              
E:link                  
The link pseudo-class                   
an E element being the source anchor of a hyperlink of which the target is not yet visited (:link) or already visited (:visited)

CSS 1              
E:visited               
The link pseudo-class                   
an E element being the source anchor of a hyperlink of which the target is not yet visited (:link) or already visited (:visited)

CSS 1              
E:active                
The link pseudo-class                   
an E element being the source anchor of a hyperlink of which the target is not yet visited (:link) or already visited (:visited)

CSS 1 and CSS 2    
E:hover                 
The user action pseudo-class            
an E element during certain user actions

CSS 1 and CSS 2    
E:focus                 
The user action pseudo-class            
an E element during certain user actions

CSS 2              
E:lang(fr)              
The :lang() pseudo-class                
an element of type E in language "fr" (the document language specifies how language is determined)

CSS 3              
E:target                
The target pseudo-class                 
an E element being the target of the referring URI

CSS 3              
E:disabled              
The UI element states pseudo-class      
a user interface element E which is enabled or disabled

CSS 3              
E:enabled               
The UI element states pseudo-class      
a user interface element E which is enabled or disabled

CSS 3              
E:checked               
The UI element states pseudo-class      
a user interface element E which is checked (for instance a radio-button or checkbox)

CSS 1              
E::first-line           
The ::first-line pseudo-element         
the first formatted line of an E element

CSS 1              
E::first-letter         
The ::first-letter pseudo-element       
the first formatted letter of an E element

CSS 2              
E::before               
The ::before pseudo-element             
generated content before an E element

CSS 2              
E::after                
The ::after pseudo-element              
generated content after an E element

CSS 3              
E::selection            
The UI element fragments pseudo-element 
the portion of an E element that is currently selected/highlighted by the user

CSS 1              
E.warning               
Class selector                          
an E element whose class is "warning" (the document language specifies how class is determined).

CSS 1              
E#myid                  
ID selector                             
an E element with ID equal to "myid".

CSS 1              
E F                     
Descendant combinator                   
an F element descendant of an E element

CSS 2              
E > F                   
Child combinator                        
an F element child of an E element

CSS 2              
E + F                   
Adjacent sibling combinator             
an F element immediately preceded by an E element

CSS 3              
E ~ F                   
General sibling combinator              
an F element preceded by an E element

CSS 3              
E:not(s)                
Negation pseudo-class                   
an E element that does not match simple selector s

CSS 2              
*                       
Universal selector                      
any element
